en_192144_0	The Inland Revenue Department said that 60,000 new tax files have been opened by 31st May since new tax laws came in to effect.
en_192144_1	Commissioner General Ivan Dissanayake said that it is expected that it would increase up to 250 thousand by the end of the year.
en_192144_2	He further said that they expect the number of tax payers to be around 3 Million by the year 2020.
